WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.711
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:02.769 --> 00:06.679
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:06.740 --> 00:08.550
the police
who investigate crime

00:08.609 --> 00:11.419
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:11.478 --> 00:13.188
These are their stories.

00:13.480 --> 00:16.090
RON: But I have a guaranteed
reservation for a suite.

00:16.149 --> 00:19.129
I'm sorry, sir, but as of midnight
the computers moved your suite

00:19.186 --> 00:20.786
into the pool of assignable rooms.
Ron...

00:20.854 --> 00:22.274
I called from the plane.
I talked to someone.

00:22.322 --> 00:23.532
IRENE: Ron, please,
this isn't helping anything.

00:23.590 --> 00:26.500
Look, what do we need, a note from the
pilot saying why we didn't make it?

00:26.560 --> 00:28.560
IRENE: This isn't helping anything.
RON: Don't you start on me, too.

00:28.629 --> 00:31.109
Just let me deal
with this gentleman.

00:31.498 --> 00:33.808
Excuse me, sir, can I help you?

00:34.134 --> 00:35.814
(IRENE GASPING)

00:37.471 --> 00:38.611
I thought he was drunk.

00:38.672 --> 00:41.212
We get all kinds wandering in
here at this hour of the morning.

00:41.275 --> 00:43.185
Maybe this one
wandered in from your bar.

00:43.243 --> 00:44.353
No, the bar is over there.

00:44.411 --> 00:45.911
He was coming from upstairs.

00:45.979 --> 00:47.959
Detective, how much longer
is this going to take?

00:48.015 --> 00:50.615
Our guests are quite sensitive
to this kind of thing.

00:50.684 --> 00:52.364
Yeah, especially this guest.

00:52.419 --> 00:54.869
In his pocket.
No ID, no wallet.

00:54.922 --> 00:57.992
Any way to find out
what room this belongs to.

00:58.158 --> 00:59.358
No, they're untraceable.

00:59.426 --> 01:00.596
A security precaution.

01:00.661 --> 01:02.331
I'm sure he appreciated it.

01:02.396 --> 01:04.995
Hey, next time there's a heart
attack at 3:00 in the morning,

01:05.065 --> 01:06.695
why don't you call it
into the 2-0?

01:06.767 --> 01:08.767
I didn't know what we got here.

01:09.570 --> 01:12.610
Before he keeled over, did you notice
if he was holding his left arm?

01:12.673 --> 01:14.153
No, he just looked drunk.

01:14.207 --> 01:15.907
BRISCOE:
Was he slurring his words?

01:16.076 --> 01:17.416
JENSEN:
No, he was trying to speak.

01:17.477 --> 01:18.887
Could be a stroke.

01:19.546 --> 01:21.486
Yeah.
How about a stroke of lead?

01:21.548 --> 01:22.748
Look at that.

01:22.816 --> 01:23.816
Jeez.

01:24.284 --> 01:26.034
Blink once and you'd miss it.

01:26.086 --> 01:27.356
Must be a small caliber.

01:27.421 --> 01:29.301
There's no exit wound.

01:29.590 --> 01:31.470
Could be a .22.
That'll do it.

01:31.525 --> 01:34.595
Ping-pongs off his vitals,
all the bleeding's internal.

01:34.661 --> 01:35.801
Great.

01:35.862 --> 01:38.872
I liked him better
when he had a heart attack.

